<div id="review_100378391" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/100378391" />
    <a title="Aloha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3081303-aloha"><img alt="Aloha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615162536p2/3081303.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/100378391?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aloha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aloha" href="/user/show/3081303-aloha">Aloha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3081303-aloha?shelf=genre-literature">genre-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3081303-aloha?shelf=z-mishima-yukio">z-mishima-yukio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3081303-aloha?shelf=a-reviewed">a-reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3081303-aloha?shelf=1-favorites">1-favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer100378391" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8836833716947953988">I read Confessions of a Mask simultaneously with Mishima: A Biography. Reading the two books dually allowed me to have a deeper insight into Mishima&apos;s life.<br/><br/>Confessions of a Mask is Mishima&apos;s personal account of his discovering of his homosexuality, his desire to fit in the conventional society, and of his grief over the fact that being part of the normal society is unattainable for him.<br/><br/>The book poignantly describes in detail his attraction to other men, in particular the philistine types, unlike</span>
  <span id="freeText8836833716947953988" style="display:none">I read Confessions of a Mask simultaneously with Mishima: A Biography. Reading the two books dually allowed me to have a deeper insight into Mishima's life.<br /><br />Confessions of a Mask is Mishima's personal account of his discovering of his homosexuality, his desire to fit in the conventional society, and of his grief over the fact that being part of the normal society is unattainable for him.<br /><br />The book poignantly describes in detail his attraction to other men, in particular the philistine types, unlike the educated Mishima. His attraction is further complicated by his obsession with death. Death, to Mishima, is the ultimate aphrodisiac. He often imagines the men he is attracted to in a tortured a bloody form, like St. Sebastian, the Christian saint and martyr. As a teenager, Mishima was aroused by the image of St. Sebastian's angelic form shot full of arrows in a painting. That image became his ultimate ideal of sexuality, with a potent combination of male beauty and death. His obsession with death is further complicated by Japan's patriotism fervor, in which death is the ultimate sacrifice. A heroic death is the ultimate attainment.<br /><br />Mishima's unusual childhood with a controlling grandmother and distant temperamental father required him to develop a strong inner world in order to emotionally survive. He was able to abstractly view his developing homosexuality, and his desire to attain what others in normal society have. He was able to distant himself and develop a "mask" of a person participating in the normal rituals of the conventional world.<br /><br />With that desire, he was able to relish in the act of courting a woman, yet all done from the viewpoint of someone observing himself. In the courtship act, his desire for normalcy, of loving a woman, of the possibility of marriage and children, became an attainable dream. However, he could not go further than the abstraction of courtship.<br /><br />Despite his ability to go through his world under a mask, a sense of grief pervades over his inability to fully join in his world.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8836833716947953988" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review100378391">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
